WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:22.000
HYD VNTG is a responsive storefront prototype with synthetic inventory, local product assets, and no payment or production-order backend.

00:22.000 --> 00:45.000
Featured items, category filters, prices, and stock labels use deterministic demo fixtures rather than real offers for sale.

00:45.000 --> 01:12.000
The Black 705 Tee opens in a labeled, keyboard-friendly dialog. Size and synthetic buyer details stay in component memory and are not intentionally stored.

01:12.000 --> 01:35.000
With no WhatsApp destination configured, submitting creates a complete local message preview labeled not sent. No popup or placeholder contact opens.

01:35.000 --> 02:08.000
Admin access is disabled by default. Local-demo credentials cannot protect real data; Supabase mode requires a server-assigned admin role and matching row-level policies.

02:08.000 --> 02:35.000
Tests cover handoff rules, catalog transitions, session rejection, admin roles, policy structure, desktop order preview, rejected admin login, and mobile overflow.

02:35.000 --> 03:02.300
The verified claim is a responsive, deterministic catalog and safe order-preparation workflow—not a live store. The public repository is canonical; the private duplicate is untouched.
